This happened to me. I was 13 at the time. I‚Äôve always been the ‚Äòbiggest‚Äô of my family. Ever since I was a preteen adults and family members would tell me to start losing weight while I was young because it was easier.
A family member of mine told me that wrapping plastic around my stomach would help me burn calories faster, so I did just that. I started exercising like crazy during summer break, maybe about 6 hours per day. I only ate small meals during the day, and I was losing weight FAST. That went on for about 2 months. Then, one morning I woke up to a strong pain coming from my abdominal area. I didn‚Äôt know what it could have been so I just took some Tylenol and went on with my day. But it kept happing every few days. Almost a year later, I was woken up because of the pain again. But it was a pain like I never experienced before. Long story short, I had to have my gallbladder removed. Now I have a strict diet I have to follow. No fatty food, no fired food, very little salt, very little spices, etc.  From that day forward, I told myself I wasn‚Äôt going to change for others but for myself. I‚Äôm still on my weight loss journey but I‚Äôm going at my pace.
